snippet.textDisplay:
Fury would have defeated Pre-Ruiz AJ but the current one is a whole different animal. Unlike Wilder, Anthony Joshua can actually box, has good leg work and devastating KO power. The funny thing is Fury has levelled up in his own way because his punching power is devastating as well, Wilder was drunk after the first knockdown. Both AJ and Fury have added something new to their arsenal. This will be such a interesting fight if it ever happens.

Wilder should concede the rematch and focus on becoming better as a boxer. Take a year off because I don’t see him improving on the same scale and timeframe as AJ did after defeat or what Fury accomplished after 3 years out of the game.

snippet.textDisplay: After seeing these fighters over the past couple of years, I give AJ next to no chance against Fury. I just can't see a way of him being able to win that fight as Fury is superior in every department. tbh, after what happened last night, I'd be surprised if AJ/Hearn even take that fight. AJ is robotic, has no inside game, is trumped in the range game and has a massive weight disadvantage. On to of that, AJ needs space to fight and Fury can chose to deny him this. imo, from the AJ perspective, he needs to stay well away from Fury. At least at the moment while Fury is on a role. I think Whyte would be a better match up for Fury due to styles.

snippet.textDisplay:
For all those Black fight fans who still make endless, non sensical ,excuses for Wilder, and being the inveterate racists that they are, who will never except the fact a mere White man could actually beat the hell out of their best, here's a thought, Fury says he's got a lot more to learn about this new aggressive style of his. He's promised that he's going to get a lot more dangerous, and Tyson Fury is 31, Wilder is 34. If there is another fight, Wilder could be permanently injured, as he would have been last night if the referee hadn't stopped the fight when he did.

I think the AJ fight could be a little tougher for Fury, but not much, this version of Fury Is getting better and better, and I don't think anybody will beat him, except maybe Fury himself.
